  "prompt": "I stopped talking to girl completely whom I love after I got to know that she got engaged to a different guy. Now her marriage has been called off and I want to ask her out. How do I do it?",
  "response": "Reaching out to someone you have feelings for, especially after a significant change in their life, can be tricky. Here are some steps to consider when asking her out:\n\n1. **Give it Some Time**: Before reaching out, give her a little space to process the recent changes in her life. She may need time to adjust after her relationship ended.\n\n2. **Re-establish Communication**: Start by reconnecting in a friendly and casual way. You could send her a message to check in and see how she\u2019s doing. This will help gauge her current feelings and establish a comfortable rapport.\n\n3. **Be Supportive**: When you talk to her, listen to how she feels about the situation. Offer your support and let her know you're there for her if she needs someone to talk to.\n\n4. **Be Honest About Your Feelings**: Once you feel that she is comfortable talking to you again, consider expressing your feelings. You might say something like, \u201cI\u2019ve always had feelings for you, and I\u2019ve realized how much I care for you.\u201d\n\n5. **Ask Her Out Casually**: If your conversation is positive and she seems receptive, suggest going out for coffee, lunch, or another low-pressure activity. For example, \u201cI\u2019d love to catch up over coffee sometime if you\u2019re interested.\u201d\n\n6. **Be Respectful and Patient**: She may still be processing her previous relationship, so be prepared for any response. If she\u2019s not ready, respect her feelings and give her the space she needs.\n\n7. **Follow Up**: If she agrees to go out with you, enjoy your time together and see where things go from there.\n\nRemember, open and honest communication is key, along with being respectful of her situation and feelings. Good luck!",
